<task id="023" project="spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5">
  <metadata>
    <title>D2-13 R5 Lead Contract Review + Sign-Off (Insights `design-e3-tool-call-contract.md` v1.0 §10)</title>
    <status>not-started</status>
    <estimated-effort>1 hour</estimated-effort>
    <actual-effort></actual-effort>
    <assigned>Operator (R5 lead) — Claude Code assists as walkthrough/checklist runner</assigned>
    <started></started>
    <completed></completed>
    <phase>Pre-Phase-2 Gate</phase>
    <wave>Pre-G6 (operator-led gate; serial; blocks Phase 2 §4.12 tasks 024–031)</wave>
    <parallel-safe>false</parallel-safe>
    <dependencies>Phase 1 complete (D1-01 through D1-09 shipped)</dependencies>
    <tags>operator-led, governance, insights, contract-review, signoff</tags>
    <rigor-level>MINIMAL</rigor-level>
  </metadata>

  <prompt>
    This task is the binding **Pre-Phase-2 gate** before R5 begins any Insights tool
    integration work (Phase 2 §4.12; tasks 024 through 031). The R5 lead reviews the
    Insights team's canonical contract document
    `projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2/design-e3-tool-call-contract.md` v1.0 and
    records six explicit contract-review decisions (D1 through D6 per spec.md §8.2) in
    that contract's §10 review log. The decisions have already been **agreed** between
    R5 and the Insights team during the 2026-06-03 v1.1 negotiation; this task is the
    operator-led act of formally recording those decisions in the contract document
    where the Insights team expects the sign-off to live, and notifying the Insights
    team that their task 042 sub-task A.5 ("Assistant team contract review") is closed.

    This is **NOT a code task**. There is no implementation, no test, no BFF publish-size
    impact. The deliverable is a documentation update in another worktree
    (`projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2/`) and an explicit notification to the
    Insights team. Claude Code's role is to walk the operator through the steps as a
    checklist, surface the exact decision text per spec §8.2 / design.md §8.2, and
    verify acceptance after the operator completes the sign-off.

    **Why this gate exists**: per CLAUDE.md §3.5 (Insights tool integration governance),
    `R5 lead MUST sign off on design-e3-tool-call-contract.md v1.0 + record 6
    contract-review decisions (D1–D6) in §10 review log BEFORE Phase 2 §4.12 work
    begins`. Per plan.md PR-04 and spec.md DR-03 / SC-10, this sign-off is a binding
    project requirement. Bypassing it leaves Phase 2 Insights work without a recorded
    contract baseline, breaks the R5↔r2 coordination protocol, and leaves Insights task
    042 sub-task A.5 open indefinitely.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    R5 lead acting as the consuming-side authority on the Insights v1.0 tool-call
    contract. Claude Code is the walkthrough assistant — it does NOT make the decisions
    (those are operator-owned, already pre-agreed per spec §8.2). Its job is to load
    the source-of-truth documents, present the six decisions verbatim, prompt the
    operator to record them in the Insights contract's §10 review log, and verify
    acceptance after the recording is done.
  </role>

  <goal>
    The Insights project's contract document
    `projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2/design-e3-tool-call-contract.md` §10 review
    log is updated to show: (a) R5 lead identity + sign-off date, (b) all six D1–D6
    decisions recorded verbatim per spec.md §8.2 / design.md §8.2 with the agreed
    outcomes ("Request v1.1 SSE", "Accept default", "Accept default", "Request v1.1
    `citations[].href`", "R5 client-side confidence badge", "Accept default"), and (c)
    a one-line cross-reference back to R5 (`spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5` task
    023). The Insights team is explicitly notified — by PR comment, by direct ping, or
    by closing the sub-task — that Insights task 042 sub-task A.5 is closed. R5
    TASK-INDEX 023 is flipped 🔲 → ✅; `current-task.md` advances to task 024 (the first
    Phase 2 §4.12 Insights tool integration task). Phase 2 §4.12 is now unblocked.
  </goal>

  <inputs>
    <file purpose="project-spec">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/spec.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-plan">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/plan.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-design">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/design.md</file>
    <file purpose="project-claude">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/CLAUDE.md</file>
    <file purpose="task-index">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md</file>
    <file purpose="integration-brief">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/insights-engine-assistant-integration-brief.md</file>
    <file purpose="v1.1-negotiation-outcome">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/insights-engine-contract-v1.1-request.md</file>
    <file purpose="insights-team-response">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/insights-team-v1.1-response.md</file>
    <file purpose="coordination-snapshot">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/insights-r2-coordination.md</file>
    <file purpose="contract-to-update" cross-worktree="true">projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2/design-e3-tool-call-contract.md</file>
    <file purpose="root-claude">CLAUDE.md</file>
  </inputs>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="plan.md PR-04">R5 lead reviews + signs off Insights `design-e3-tool-call-contract.md` v1.0 BEFORE Phase 2 §4.12 Insights tool integration work begins. This is a hard gate — tasks 024 through 031 MUST NOT start until this task is ✅.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec.md DR-03">R5 lead signs off on Insights `design-e3-tool-call-contract.md` v1.0 and records 6 contract-review decisions (D1–D6 per design.md §8.2) in the contract's §10 review log. Closes Insights task 042 sub-task A.5.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec.md SC-10">R5 lead has reviewed `design-e3-tool-call-contract.md` v1.0 and recorded 6 contract-review decisions (D1–D6) in contract's §10 review log. Closes Insights task 042 sub-task A.5.</constraint>
    <constraint source="CLAUDE.md §3.5">R5 lead MUST sign off on `projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2/design-e3-tool-call-contract.md` v1.0 + record 6 contract-review decisions (D1–D6 per spec.md §8.2) in §10 review log BEFORE Phase 2 §4.12 work begins. R5 is Zone B consumer of HTTP contract only.</constraint>
    <constraint source="spec.md §8.2">The six decisions are pre-agreed per the 2026-06-03 v1.1 negotiation: D1 = Request v1.1 SSE; D2 = Accept default (forceMode without playbook hint resolves to `predict-matter-cost@v1`); D3 = Accept default (decline rendering plain strings in v1; actionable buttons → R6); D4 = Request v1.1 `citations[].href` (Wave F 0.5d spike confirms schema plumbing; fallback to display-name-only if plumbing > 1d); D5 = R5 implements client-side confidence badge (`confidence < 0.6` → "Low confidence"; no contract change); D6 = Accept default (`previousTurnSummary` logged only in v1; classifier Phase 2 may consume in R6).</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Operator MUST record the decisions verbatim with the exact wording above. Paraphrasing risks downstream misalignment with the Insights team.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Cross-worktree edit semantics: the contract doc lives in the Insights project worktree (`projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2/`). The operator MAY edit cross-worktree directly OR coordinate via a PR comment on the Insights team's open PR for contract v1.0 (whichever the Insights team prefers per coordination snapshot). The act of recording is the same either way.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-029">BFF publish hygiene — this task adds NO BFF code and NO infrastructure. Publish-size delta = 0 MB; no `dotnet publish` measurement required. Confirm in task notes.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-010">DI minimalism — N/A for this task (no service registrations, no Program.cs changes).</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <topic>governance/contract-review-signoff</topic>
    <files>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/spec.md (§8.2 contract-review decisions table — verbatim source for D1–D6)</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/design.md (§8.2 design-side rationale for D1–D6)</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/insights-engine-assistant-integration-brief.md (v1.0 contract baseline)</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/insights-engine-contract-v1.1-request.md §0a (Insights team negotiation outcome — confirms D1, D4 path)</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/insights-team-v1.1-response.md (Insights team's 7-point feedback integrated)</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/insights-r2-coordination.md (R5↔r2 coordination snapshot; §8 changelog)</file>
      <file>projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2/design-e3-tool-call-contract.md (the document being edited; §10 review log is the target section)</file>
    </files>
    <patterns>
      <pattern name="Six-decision verbatim text" location="spec.md §8.2 table rows for D1 through D6">
        Each decision must be recorded with: (a) decision ID (D1–D6), (b) the question
        being decided (left column of spec §8.2 table), (c) the agreed outcome (right
        column, sometimes prefixed with **Request v1.1** or **Accept default**), (d)
        rationale snippet, (e) FR/NFR cross-reference. Claude Code surfaces this verbatim
        in Step 3 below; the operator copies it into §10.
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Cross-worktree coordination" location="notes/insights-r2-coordination.md §8 changelog">
        Per coordination protocol, milestones touching either project are mirrored in the
        coordination doc's §8 changelog. Add a one-line entry after sign-off:
        "2026-MM-DD — R5 lead signed off `design-e3-tool-call-contract.md` v1.0 §10;
        D1–D6 recorded; Insights task 042 sub-task A.5 closed; Phase 2 §4.12 unblocked."
      </pattern>
      <pattern name="Insights team notification" location="N/A — operator action">
        Three acceptable mechanisms (operator picks one based on Insights team's
        preference at the moment of sign-off): (1) comment on the Insights team's open
        PR for contract v1.0 with link to the §10 entry, (2) ping in shared coordination
        channel referencing the §10 line, (3) directly tick the Insights task 042
        sub-task A.5 in the Insights project's TASK-INDEX. Whichever path is used, log
        which one in R5 task notes for audit.
      </pattern>
    </patterns>
  </knowledge>

  <context>
    <background>
      The Insights Engine R2 project shipped a Phase 1.5 read-only single-shot v1.0
      tool-call contract (`POST /api/insights/assistant/query`) via Wave E3 task 042
      on 2026-06-03. The Insights team's task 042 explicitly carries a sub-task A.5
      requiring "Assistant team contract review" — this is the consuming team (R5)
      signing off on the contract shape, scopes, error codes, and routing decisions
      before R5 starts implementing the consumer side. On 2026-06-03 late, R5 design
      review (`design.md` / `spec.md` §8.2) made the six pre-agreed decisions across
      the open contract questions (v1.1 SSE; forceMode default; decline rendering;
      clickable citations; confidence badge; previousTurnSummary). Those decisions
      were communicated to the Insights team via the v1.1 request document
      (`notes/insights-engine-contract-v1.1-request.md`); the Insights team responded
      with 7 feedback points (all integrated in §0a), and Wave F (v1.1 minor-version
      implementation) was approved by the operator on 2026-06-03 late for parallel
      execution. **The remaining missing step is the formal recording**: putting the
      six decisions into the Insights contract's §10 review log so the Insights team
      has a durable artifact that R5 has signed off. Until this is done, Insights task
      042 sub-task A.5 stays open and R5's Phase 2 §4.12 tasks (024–031) are formally
      blocked even though the negotiated content is already settled.
    </background>
    <dependencies>
      <dependency task="Phase 1 (D1-01 → D1-09)" status="complete">
        All Phase 1 platform-extension tasks ✅. This gate is the first task of the
        Pre-Phase-2 transition.
      </dependency>
      <dependency task="External — Insights R2 Wave E3 task 042" status="complete">
        Insights team shipped the v1.0 contract document on 2026-06-03 via PR #337;
        the `design-e3-tool-call-contract.md` file exists and has a §10 review log
        section ready to receive R5's sign-off.
      </dependency>
    </dependencies>
    <related-work>
      <item>The 2026-06-03 v1.1 negotiation (`notes/insights-engine-contract-v1.1-request.md`
        §0a + `notes/insights-team-v1.1-response.md`) pre-decided D1 and D4 substance.
        This task is the formal record-keeping step, not a new negotiation.</item>
      <item>R5↔r2 coordination protocol (`notes/insights-r2-coordination.md` §8 changelog)
        — every cross-project milestone is mirrored there. Sign-off is one such
        milestone.</item>
      <item>Tasks 024 through 031 (Phase 2 §4.12 Insights tool integration suite —
        `InsightsQueryToolHandler`, subject resolution, two-path renderer, clickable
        citations, error codes, smoke tests) are formally blocked on this task. The
        first downstream task is 024 (D2-14 `InsightsQueryToolHandler` chat-agent tool
        function).</item>
    </related-work>
  </context>

  <steps>
    <step order="0" name="Context Check + Rigor Declaration">
      Check context usage. If &gt; 70%, create handoff and request `/compact`.
      Output verbatim:
      ```
      🔒 RIGOR LEVEL: MINIMAL
      📋 REASON: Operator-led governance task — no code, no tests, no infrastructure
         change. Documentation update in another worktree + Insights team notification +
         TASK-INDEX status flip. No FULL-rigor quality gates required per CLAUDE.md §8.
      📖 PROTOCOL STEPS TO EXECUTE: 0 → 1 → 2 → 3 → 4 → 5 → 6 → 7
      Proceeding with Step 0...
      ```
    </step>

    <step order="1" name="Review Contract v1.0 (Source-of-Truth Walkthrough)">
      Claude Code reads the Insights v1.0 contract document
      `projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2/design-e3-tool-call-contract.md` and the
      R5-side integration brief
      `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/insights-engine-assistant-integration-brief.md`.
      Output a brief walkthrough for the operator covering: (a) the endpoint surface
      (`POST /api/insights/assistant/query`), (b) the request/response envelope shape,
      (c) the 12 binding error codes, (d) the playbook-vs-RAG routing model, (e) where
      §10 review log lives in the contract document. The operator confirms they
      recognize each — no decisions made here; this is the orientation pass.
    </step>

    <step order="2" name="Review v1.1 Negotiation Outcome (Pre-Agreed Decisions Recap)">
      Claude Code reads both
      `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/insights-engine-contract-v1.1-request.md`
      §0a (R5-side negotiated agreement) and
      `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/insights-team-v1.1-response.md`
      (Insights team's 7-point feedback) and recaps to the operator: (a) D1 SSE
      accepted as v1.1 minor; (b) D4 `citations[].href` accepted with 0.5d Wave F
      spike to confirm plumbing; (c) Wave F sized at ~4.5d Insights engineering,
      operator-approved 2026-06-03 late, in flight via Claude Code; (d) graceful v1.0
      fallback exists for both v1.1 features per spec NFR-11. Operator confirms they
      recognize the v1.1 outcome — still no recording action; this is context for the
      next step.
    </step>

    <step order="3" name="Record D1–D6 Decisions in Contract §10 Review Log">
      Claude Code prints the six decision entries verbatim, one block per decision,
      using the exact wording derived from `spec.md` §8.2 / `design.md` §8.2:

      ```
      ### Review log entry — R5 lead sign-off, {YYYY-MM-DD}

      Reviewer: R5 lead ({operator name})
      Consuming project: spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5 (task 023)
      Contract under review: design-e3-tool-call-contract.md v1.0

      **D1 — SSE on `/api/insights/assistant/query`**
      Question: Accept default (no SSE) or request v1.1 minor-version SSE?
      Decision: **REQUEST v1.1 SSE**.
      Rationale: R5 has FieldDelta SSE infrastructure for Summarize; reusing the same
      protocol gives the chat agent uniform streaming UX across AI tools. v1.0 single-shot
      fallback retained per spec NFR-11.
      Cross-reference: FR-13 + NFR-11.

      **D2 — `forceMode` without playbook hint**
      Question: Accept default (BFF resolves to `predict-matter-cost@v1`)?
      Decision: **ACCEPT DEFAULT**.
      Rationale: R5 will not blind-fire `forceMode` without a known intent. The default
      fallback playbook is acceptable.
      Cross-reference: FR-17.

      **D3 — Decline rendering**
      Question: Plain strings or actionable verbs?
      Decision: **ACCEPT DEFAULT** — plain strings in v1.
      Rationale: Actionable button affordances deferred to R6 backlog. Plain strings
      adequate for Phase 1.5.
      Cross-reference: FR-13 (Decline case).

      **D4 — Clickable citations (`citations[].href`)**
      Question: Accept default (display-name only) or request `citations[].href`?
      Decision: **REQUEST v1.1 `citations[].href`**.
      Rationale: Clickable citations close major trust gap. Insights Wave F includes
      0.5d spike to confirm schema plumbing; fallback to display-name-only `href` if
      document-citation plumbing is large; document `href` defers to v1.2 if needed.
      Cross-reference: FR-14 + NFR-11.

      **D5 — Confidence floor / low-confidence badge**
      Question: Accept default (no badge) or implement client-side badge?
      Decision: **IMPLEMENT CLIENT-SIDE** — `confidence < 0.6` → "Low confidence" badge.
      Rationale: Pure R5 client-side work; no contract change required.
      Cross-reference: FR-15.

      **D6 — `previousTurnSummary` to classifier**
      Question: Accept default (logged only)?
      Decision: **ACCEPT DEFAULT**.
      Rationale: Phase 2 of classifier may consume `previousTurnSummary` in R6; R5 v1
      does not need it.
      Cross-reference: (no FR impact in R5 v1).
      ```

      The operator then either: (a) edits
      `projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2/design-e3-tool-call-contract.md` §10
      directly cross-worktree (Claude Code uses the Edit tool to insert the block at
      the appropriate spot in §10), OR (b) posts the block as a PR comment on the
      Insights team's open contract PR for them to integrate, per coordination
      preference. The operator confirms which path was taken; Claude Code records the
      path in task notes (Step 7).
    </step>

    <step order="4" name="Confirm Sign-Off Date + R5 Lead Identity">
      Operator confirms: (a) sign-off date (today, expected 2026-06-04 or 2026-06-05);
      (b) R5 lead identity string used in the review log entry header (e.g., "Ralph
      Schroeder" or the agreed pseudonymous label per coordination convention). Claude
      Code verifies the §10 review log block (or PR comment) contains both values
      explicitly and matches them against the date emitted by the system clock.
    </step>

    <step order="5" name="Notify Insights Team — Close Their Task 042 Sub-Task A.5">
      Operator picks one notification mechanism (per knowledge §"Insights team
      notification" pattern):
      1. **PR comment** on the Insights team's open contract PR linking to the §10
         entry just added; OR
      2. **Coordination channel ping** referencing the §10 line; OR
      3. **Direct sub-task tick** in the Insights project's TASK-INDEX (task 042
         sub-task A.5 → ✅) if cross-worktree edit is preferred.

      Claude Code helps execute whichever mechanism is chosen. The operator confirms
      the Insights team has been notified. Add a one-line entry to
      `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/insights-r2-coordination.md`
      §8 changelog:
      ```
      - YYYY-MM-DD — R5 lead signed off `design-e3-tool-call-contract.md` v1.0 §10;
        D1–D6 recorded; Insights task 042 sub-task A.5 closed; Phase 2 §4.12 unblocked
        (R5 task 023 ✅).
      ```
    </step>

    <step order="6" name="Update TASK-INDEX Status">
      Edit `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md`: flip
      task 023 status 🔲 → ✅. Verify no other R5 tasks were accidentally touched.
      Confirm tasks 024 through 031 (Phase 2 §4.12) now show their dependency on 023
      as satisfied — they remain 🔲 (not started) but are no longer formally blocked.
    </step>

    <step order="7" name="Document + Complete">
      Update this POML's `<status>` to `complete`, fill in `<completed>` date and
      `<actual-effort>`. Reset `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/current-task.md`
      to point to task 024 (D2-14 `InsightsQueryToolHandler`) per CLAUDE.md §7. Write
      a short notes file
      `projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/task-023-signoff-evidence.md`
      capturing: (a) sign-off date, (b) R5 lead identity used, (c) which path was used
      to record (cross-worktree edit vs PR comment vs sub-task tick), (d) which
      notification mechanism was used, (e) one-line confirmation each of D1–D6 was
      recorded verbatim, (f) link/anchor to the §10 review log entry, (g) BFF
      publish-size delta = 0 MB (no BFF code touched). Report task completion to the
      operator with the next task (024) called out as ready to start.
    </step>
  </steps>

  <tools>
    <tool name="Read">Read v1.0 contract, integration brief, v1.1 negotiation outcome, spec §8.2, design §8.2.</tool>
    <tool name="Edit">Insert the §10 review log entry into the Insights project's contract document (cross-worktree edit path); update TASK-INDEX status; update coordination doc §8 changelog.</tool>
    <tool name="Write">Create the task-023 evidence notes file under `notes/`.</tool>
    <tool name="git">Stage + commit the documentation changes on the R5 branch (and, if cross-worktree edit was used, on the Insights worktree's branch per its conventions). Operator-supervised — Claude Code does NOT commit autonomously for this task.</tool>
  </tools>

  <outputs>
    <output type="docs" cross-worktree="true">projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2/design-e3-tool-call-contract.md §10 review log — NEW entry with R5 lead sign-off + D1–D6 verbatim</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/insights-r2-coordination.md §8 changelog — NEW one-line sign-off entry</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/tasks/TASK-INDEX.md — status: 023 🔲 → ✅</output>
    <output type="docs">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/current-task.md — reset to next pending task (024 D2-14)</output>
    <output type="notes" ephemeral="true">projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r5/notes/task-023-signoff-evidence.md — recording path, notification mechanism, D1–D6 verification, §10 anchor</output>
    <output type="external-action">Insights team notified via PR comment / coordination channel / direct sub-task tick; Insights task 042 sub-task A.5 closed</output>
    <output type="report">Task completion report (Step 7) — surfaces task 024 as the next ready task</output>
  </outputs>

  <acceptance-criteria>
    <criterion testable="true">`projects/ai-spaarke-insights-engine-r2/design-e3-tool-call-contract.md` §10 review log contains a NEW entry headed with R5 lead identity + sign-off date and dated within ±2 days of task 023 execution.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">All six decisions D1, D2, D3, D4, D5, D6 are recorded in the §10 entry with the exact decision outcomes ("REQUEST v1.1 SSE", "ACCEPT DEFAULT", "ACCEPT DEFAULT", "REQUEST v1.1 `citations[].href`", "IMPLEMENT CLIENT-SIDE", "ACCEPT DEFAULT" respectively) per spec.md §8.2.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Each decision entry includes the question being decided + rationale snippet + FR/NFR cross-reference per the Step 3 template.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">Insights task 042 sub-task A.5 is explicitly closed (via one of the three notification mechanisms in Step 5); the chosen mechanism is recorded in `notes/task-023-signoff-evidence.md`.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`notes/insights-r2-coordination.md` §8 changelog contains a NEW one-line sign-off entry dated within ±2 days of task 023 execution, referencing R5 task 023 ✅ and Phase 2 §4.12 unblock.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`tasks/TASK-INDEX.md` shows task 023 status as ✅; tasks 024 through 031 remain 🔲 (not started) but are no longer formally blocked.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`current-task.md` has been reset to point to the next pending task (expected: 024 D2-14 `InsightsQueryToolHandler`).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">`notes/task-023-signoff-evidence.md` exists and records: sign-off date, R5 lead identity used, recording path (cross-worktree edit vs PR comment vs sub-task tick), notification mechanism used, per-decision verification (D1–D6), §10 anchor/link, and BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB.</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">BFF publish-size delta = 0 MB (confirmed in evidence notes; no BFF code touched by this task).</criterion>
    <criterion testable="true">spec.md SC-10 acceptance criterion is now satisfiable (R5 lead has reviewed v1.0 + recorded D1–D6 + closed Insights sub-task A.5).</criterion>
  </acceptance-criteria>
</task>
